text.section:
As used in this section, unless the context requires otherwise:
"Step therapy" means a protocol that establishes the specific sequence in which prescription drugs for a specified medical condition and medically appropriate for a particular patient are to be prescribed;
"Fail-first protocol" has the same meaning as step therapy in paragraph (a) of this subsection;
"Override of the restriction" means the permission to deviate from the required sequence by prescribing another drug that is medically necessary; and
"Insurer" has the same meaning as in KRS 304.17A-005.
